AttributeList.Text:
//In tracking-stations you normally use a fast counting-card to count the
//conveyor-pulses. The length-increment - the way the conveyor moved since
//the last block-cycle - is calculated by means of a coveyor-scaling-factor.
//You can use this FB to calc the length increment.
//
//HANDLED SITUATIONS:
//- pulse-peak detection - unnormal high pulse-peaks will be ignored and cause a
//  reset
//- counting forward, counting backward
//- overflow handling forward/backward at 2147483647/-2147483647
//- no division-error (division-remainder is considered in next cycle)
//
//INSTRUCTIONS:
//- init/reset with a rising edge on "i_mRun" or "i_mReset". The current conveyor
//  pulse count will be saved (internal) to avoid a pulse-peak
//- set the value of the conveyor-counting-var as input-parameter of this FB
//- set the max tolerable pulse-peak between two cycles as input-parameter
//  for error-detection (approx. 4-10 times higher than the normal amount of
//  pulses per cycle).
//
//SPEED CALCULATION:
//The speed will be updated with a time-interval, which can be defined with the 
//parameter "i_tSpeedCalcIntvl". Note: If you have a fast counting card the 
//time-parameter may be low (e.g. 1-2s) so you get a fast update of the calculated
//speed. If you have a slow counting-card (e.g. with impulse-division-card) you
//should use a higher time-value. Of course the update of the time-value will
//be more slow.
//
//CONVEYOR RUNNING:
//The output-parameter "conveyor-running" is true, when the calculated conveyor-
//increments are unequal to zero. This signal will be debounced with the time-
//parameter "i_tConvRunDeb".
